perl-io-html: IO::HTML provides an easy way to open a file containing HTML while
perl-io-html: automatically determining its encoding. It uses the HTML5 encoding
perl-io-html: sniffing algorithm specified in section 8.2.2.1 of the draft
perl-io-html: standard.
